Today, the House of Representatives held a moment of silence to honor the lives of three fallen Northern York County Regional Police officers who tragically lost their lives in the line of duty on Wednesday, September 17.

Det. Sgt. Cody Becker
Det. Mark Baker
Det. Isaiah Emenheiser

The Pennsylvania Delegation, along with the entire House of Representatives, mourns this tragic loss. Our hearts and prayers are with the families, loved ones, fellow officers, and our entire York County community during this difficult time.

Thank you to @WaysandMeansGOP for PASSING my Social Security Child Protection Act. In 2022, 1.7 million children were victims of identity theft. This bill would require the SSA to issue a new SSN to a child under 14 years of age if the card is lost or stolen in the mail, preventing fraud before it happens.

Proud to have my Claiming Age Clarity Act pass through @WaysandMeansGOP committee with strong bipartisan support. This simple, yet powerful bill helps Americans better understand their Social Security retirement benefit options. 

Thanks for the support @AARP, @AMACforAmerica, @BPC_Bipartisan

I am devastated and heartbroken by the senseless and horrific tragedy that unfolded today in North Codorus Township. We mourn the brave officers who lost their lives in the line of duty, and we extend our deepest sympathies and prayers to their families and loved ones. Tonight, families are facing the unimaginable pain of loved ones not returning home and there is a profound sense of loss felt by our entire community. 

We ask everyone to keep the Northern York Regional Police Department, York County Sheriff’s Office, and all first responders across our community in your thoughts and prayers, as they grieve the loss of their fellow officers. We hope for the swift recovery of the injured officers and are grateful to the dedicated medical professionals providing their care. Our community will come together to support our brave law enforcement officers and all who are affected by today’s tragedy.

I'm proud to cosponsor the Hospital Inpatient Services Modernization Act (H.R. 4313), which PASSED through @WaysandMeansGOP committee today. 

This bill provides high-quality care to patients in the comfort of their homes, improving recovery outcomes and lowering costs for Americans. 

CC: @VernBuchanan @RepDwightEvans

Americans deserve clear, straightforward information when making important financial decisions about their future.

This bill clarifies the Social Security Administration’s language to more directly explain how age affects retirement benefits:

Early Eligibility Age ➡️ Minimum Benefit Age
Full Retirement Age ➡️ Standard Benefit Age
Delayed Retirement Age ➡️ Maximum Benefit Age

Better terms = Better choices

This week, @RepDonBeyer and I introduced the Claiming Age Clarity Act to help seniors better understand their Social Security retirement options.

It was an honor to take part in the closing ceremony of York County’s 275th anniversary celebration on Tuesday.

York has always held a special place in our nation's story. From serving as the nation's capital during the Revolutionary War to being the birthplace of the Articles of Confederation—which laid the foundation for the U.S. Constitution and many of the freedoms we cherish today—this vibrant community has stood tall during some of our country’s most defining moments.

As we reflect on 275 years of rich history, resilience, and patriotism, we also look to the future and the generations who will continue shaping our community for the next 275 years and beyond.

I am truly proud to represent York County in Congress.

Happy Capital Day, Lancaster! On September 27, 1777, the Continental Congress met in the old Lancaster County Courthouse after fleeing Philadelphia which had been occupied by British soldiers during the Revolutionary War. The Continental Congress would then head west, meeting in York until late June 1778. https://t.co/7Vb8zgevio
